            <p>You must provide a copy of the completed CP12 to your tenants within 28 days of the inspection being carried out.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="obligation-item">
          <div class="obligation-icon">3</div>
          <div>
            <strong>New tenants must receive certificate before moving in</strong>
            <p>Before a new tenant takes up residence, they must be given a copy of the current gas safety certificate. This is a legal requirement, not a courtesy.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="obligation-item">
          <div class="obligation-icon">4</div>
          <div>
            <strong>Keep records for at least two years</strong>
            <p>Landlords must retain copies of all gas safety certificates for a minimum of two years. Liverpool City Council can request these at any time.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="obligation-item">
          <div class="obligation-icon">5</div>
          <div>
            <strong>Applies to all gas appliances you provide</strong>
            <p>The obligation covers all gas appliances supplied as part of the tenancy: boilers, gas cookers, gas fires and gas hobs. If you supply it, you are responsible for it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="penalty-box">
        <h3>Penalties for Non-Compliance</h3>
