          <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Yes. Under the <a href="https://www.hse.gov.uk/gas/landlords/index.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Gas Safety (Installation and Use) Regulations 1998</a>, all landlords in England must have a valid CP12 certificate for every rental property with gas appliances. The certificate must be renewed every 12 months. Non-compliance risks fines up to £6,000 per property and in serious cases criminal prosecution. <a href="https://liverpool.gov.uk/housing/landlords/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Liverpool City Council</a> actively enforces gas safety compliance.</p>
