          <div class="faq-body">
            <p>A standard gas safety check covering one boiler takes 30 to 45 minutes. Properties with additional gas appliances such as a gas cooker or gas fire take slightly longer. You or your tenant do not need to be present for the entire inspection, just to provide access at the start.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary><span class="faq-tag tag-navy">DIFFERENCE</span>What is the difference between a gas safety certificate and a boiler service?</summary>
          <div class="faq-body">
            <p>They are two different things. A gas safety certificate (CP12) is a legal safety check confirming all gas appliances are safe to use. It does not clean or maintain the boiler. A boiler service is a maintenance check ensuring the boiler runs efficiently and safely. We recommend combining both on the same visit for £120 to save time and money.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
