          <h2>Gas Safety Certificates for Liverpool Landlords</h2>
          <h3 style="color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin:0.75rem 0 0.4rem;text-align:center;">Why is the CP12 so important?</h3>
          <p>The CP12 is not just a legal box to tick. A gas safety check carried out by a qualified engineer is the only reliable way to confirm that your tenants are not at risk from gas leaks, carbon monoxide poisoning or faulty appliances. According to the <a href="https://www.hse.gov.uk/gas/domestic/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HSE</a>, around 40 people die from accidental carbon monoxide poisoning in England and Wales every year, many from faulty gas appliances. The CP12 inspection exists to catch these faults before they become fatal.</p>
          <h3 style="color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin:0.75rem 0 0.4rem;text-align:center;">How to choose a gas safety engineer in Liverpool</h3>
          <p>Always verify the engineer is Gas Safe registered before allowing them to inspect your property. It is illegal for an unregistered person to carry out gas work or issue a CP12 certificate. You can check any engineer's registration at <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">gassaferegister.co.uk</a>. All Ideal Plumbing Solutions engineers carry their Gas Safe ID card and you are welcome to verify their registration on arrival.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="copy-block">
          <h2>Liverpool's Rental Market and Gas Safety Compliance</h2>
          <h3 style="color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin:0.75rem 0 0.4rem;text-align:center;">How many rental properties are there in Liverpool?</h3>
          <p>Liverpool has one of the largest private rental sectors in England, with a high concentration of student lets, HMOs and traditional private rentals particularly around the city centre, Anfield, Wavertree and the university areas. <a href="https://liverpool.gov.uk/housing/landlords/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Liverpool City Council</a> actively enforces gas safety compliance and inspects landlords following tenant complaints. Having an up-to-date CP12 is the simplest protection against enforcement action.</p>
          <h3 style="color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin:0.75rem 0 0.4rem;text-align:center;">What are letting agents required to check?</h3>
          <p>Liverpool letting agents are required to confirm that a valid gas safety certificate is in place before letting a property. Most reputable letting agents will not place tenants in a property without a current CP12. See <a href="https://www.citizensadvice.org.uk/housing/renting-privately/during-your-tenancy/gas-safety-checks/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Citizens Advice guidance on gas safety in rented properties</a> for tenant rights information.</p>
